  "doc_id": "55019",
  "text": "The Augmentation Index (AIx) was estimated using an oscillometric Mobil-O-Graph (Stolberg, Germany) [CITATION_1] . The measurements of central SBP (cSBP) and peripheral SBP (pSBP) were taken in the dominant arm. Arm circumference was measured and recorded to allow for the correct choice of cuff size (two sizes available: 24-34 and 32-42 cm). With a conventional cuff, the determination of the cSBP is based on an oscillometric BP measurement and uses the pulse waves assessed at the brachial artery. After estimating the pBP, the cuff instantly re-inflates and recordings of the cSBP are performed at DBP levels for 10 s [CITATION_2] . From the morphology of the aortic wave, the AIx was estimated using the following formula: increase in central pressure × 100/pulse pressure. The values were adjusted to a heart rate of 75 (AIx_75) by the Mobil-O-Graph device [CITATION_3] .",
